init_text:
Are We Being Bad Citizens If We Don't Keep Up With the News?

In your opinion, are we being bad citizens if we don't keep up with the news? Do you think all people have some responsibility to know what is going on in the world? Does engaging with current events actually do anything at all? Why do you think the way you do?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The news can deceive some people by making them believe that all of society is bad and horrible.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: So if we live near a major crime area, we probably want to listen to the news to learn about that area.

actions.name: text-delete
actions.text: So if we live near a major crime area, we probably want to listen to the news to learn about that area.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: If anything, keeping up with the news should have a moral implication if you happen to miss a story from people from your community.
